race.comment: A QUEENS BUZZ (10) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest beaten 1L here over 1390m. Has the rail and the switch to a top hoop and is suitably placed to win. ALPINE WHISKEY (1) led and was nudged out at Launceston over this distance. Peaks now and from a handy draw can go one better. SEDITIOUS AWARD (8) was knocking on the door before getting too far back at Launceston. Draws wide but she's capable of making the finish if she enjoys some luck. SH'BOURNE RISING (9) ran a promising race here three back and hasn't had the best of it since. Still lightly raced and keep onside. JOEJOE (5) trialled six times before his race debut and did a good job here after settling back. Will have to do it the hard way, but will have taken fitness and learning and should be around the mark.
